      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:90:1",
      "text": [
        " يَجِبُ لِلْمُؤْمِنِ عَلَى الْمُؤْمِنِ أَنْ يُنَاصِحَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Umar Bin Aban, from Isa Bin Abu Mansour, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘It is an Obligation for the <span class=\"iTxt\">Momin</span> upon the <span class=\"iTxt\">Momin</span> that he advises him’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn al-Hakam from ‘Umar ibn Aban from ‘Isa ibn abu Mansur from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “It is of a believer’s obligations to provide good advice to another believer.” "
        ]
      }
